		<body>
			<div type="transcription">
				<div type="original" xml:lang="pl">
					<!--<p>Relacja <persName ref="#ehri_et_munzer_efroim">Efroima Münzera</persName> (sygn.
        301/203)</p>
      <p>Oryginał, rękopis, 4 strony, 150 x 210 mm, język polski</p>-->
					<p><pb facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010203_01.jpg" n="1"/><persName ref="#ehri_et_munzer_efroim">Efroim Münzer</persName>, urodzony <date when="1928-01-01">1. 1. 1928</date> w <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/772270/gdow.html">Gdowie</placeName>, miasteczo <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/6690166/powiat-wielicki.html">powiat wielicki</placeName></p>
					<p>zawód: piekarz</p>
					<p>zamieszkały: <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3094802/krakow.html">ulica Starowiślna 66 mieszkania 17</placeName> w <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3094802/krakow.html">Krakowie</placeName></p>
					<p>Opis <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">obozu</term> i <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-486" type="subject">życia</term> w <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/758445/stalowa-wola.html">Stalowej
							Woli</placeName></p>
					<p>W <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">obozie</term> przebywał od roku <date when="1942">1942</date> – <date when="1944">1944</date>. W <date when="1942-08">sierpniu 1942</date> podczas <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-115" type="subject">wysiedlenia</term> we <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/755889/wieliczka.html">Wieliczce</placeName> załadowano go do <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522"
							type="subject">wagonów</term> towarowych, po 100 osób w <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject">wagonie</term>. Jechał 24 godziny podczas upalnego okresu bez dopuszczenia kogoś z napojem. Tylko w <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/773380/debica.html">Dębicy</placeName> jeden <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_poles">Polak</term> podał im wiadro wody za opłatą 100 złotych. Po przybyciu do <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject"
							>obozu</term> przyjęła ich <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-480" type="subject">straż obozowa</term>, składająca się z <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_belarusians">Białorusinów</term> z <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-564" type="subject">nahajkami</term>. Dla <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1057" type="subject">pracujących</term> były 3 <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">baraki</term>. W <date when="1942-08">sierpniu 1942</date> było tam 80 Żydów z <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/759301/sieniawa.html">Sieniawy</placeName>. <date when="1942-08">Od
							sierpnia</date> już 680 (600 z <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/755889/wieliczka.html">Wieliczki</placeName>). W <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">barakach</term> były prycze bez sienników, tak że <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">robotnicy</term> spali tam na deskach. W pierwszym dniu <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">robotnicy</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-653" type="subject">stali</term> przed <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">barakiem</term> od piątej rano do wieczora. Podczas tego czasu rewidowano ich gruntownie i
						odebrano <pb facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010203_02.jpg" n="2"/> im wszystko, od <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660" type="subject">pieniędzy</term>, kosztowności aż do zwykłego skórzanego paska. Wieczorem doszedł do nich <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS Scharführer</term>
						<persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000364">Schwamberg</persName> (znany jako likwidator <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">getta</term> w <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/761168/przemysl.html">Przemyślu</placeName>) i <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject"><foreign xml:lang="de">Unterscharführer</foreign></term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_bardok">Brzdok</persName> (prawdopodobnie <persName ref="#ehri_et_bardok">Bardok</persName>). <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000364">Schwamberg</persName> wygłosił mowę: Trzeba oddać wszystkie kosztowności. Kto się
						zbliży do drutów, automatycznie zostaje <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">zastrzelony</term>. Kto z Żydów podczas pracy będzie mówił z cywilistą<note type="gloss">Właściwie: cywilem.</note> przy <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">pracy</term>, może o sprzedaży <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">chleba</term> lub innej sprawie, zostanie <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">rozstrzelony</term>. Kto będzie stał przy <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">pracy</term>, zostanie <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">rozstrzelony</term>.</p>
					<p>Zaraz po tej mowie większość wyrzuciła ukryte pieniądze lub <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660" type="subject">kosztowności</term>. Podczas tego, by odstraszyć, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-653" type="subject"
							>zbito</term> do krwi kilku ludzi rzekomo dlatego, gdyż nie oddali wszystkiego. O drugiej w nocy była <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-486" type="subject">pobudka</term>. Wymarsz do <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">pracy</term> zaczął się o 6 godzinie, do tego czasu stali wszyscy. Każdemu zabrano <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">czapki</term> i <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">marynarki</term>, by im w ten sposób uniemożliwić <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">ucieczkę</term>. Do <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">pracy</term> do <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-929" type="subject">fabryki</term> w odległości 4 kilometrów goniono <pb facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010203_03.jpg" n="3"/>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-564" type="subject">nahajkami</term>. Tylko biegiem. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">Praca</term> trwała od 7 rano do 6 wieczorem z przerwą 20-minutową o godzinie
						3-ciej na zjedzenie <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">zupy</term>. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">Pracowali</term> w <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-929" type="subject">stalowni</term>. <foreign xml:lang="de">Vorarbeiterami</foreign> przy <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">pracy</term> byli <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1075" type="subject">Volksdeutsche</term>. Największym sadystą wśród nich był <persName ref="#ehri_et_piosik">Piosik</persName> (podobno z <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3088171/poznan.html"
							>Poznania</placeName>). On <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">mordował</term> Żydów <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-533" type="subject">kawałkiem żelaza</term>. Raz <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-533" type="subject">spalił żywcem</term> jednego Żyda. Najwięcej Żydów <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">ginęło</term> z powodu powyższego <persName
							ref="#ehri_et_piosik">Piosika</persName>. Codziennie <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">uciekało</term> prawie 8 – 10 Żydów z miejsca pracy. Z tego powodu musieli codziennie prawie <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-653" type="subject">stać</term> wszyscy 2 – 3 godziny podczas <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-487" type="subject">apelu</term>. Wieczorem otrzymali około 20 dekagramów <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">chleba</term> i <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">zupę</term>, w której były brudne i nieobłupane <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">ziemniaki.</term> Na czele <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">baraku</term> stał <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-566"
							type="subject">
							<foreign xml:lang="de">Ordnungsdienstmann</foreign></term>. Prawie codziennie <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">zastrzeliwano</term> 10 – 15 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject"
							>chorych</term>, leżących w tak zwanej <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-491" type="subject">Krankenstube</term>. Te <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">morderstwa</term> popełniał jeden <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-Sturmmann</term>. W <date when="1942-12">grudniu 1942</date>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">rozstrzelono</term> 121 lub 123 Żydów jako niezdolnych do <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">pracy</term>. Oprócz tego <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">umierało</term> też codziennie 10 – 15 ludzi <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">(dezynteria)</term> i tym podobne). (<date when="1942-09">Od
							września</date> było już tam 1100 Żydów). <pb facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010203_04.jpg" n="4"/> Na czele <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-566" type="subject">O[rdnungs] D[ienst]</term> stał Żyd <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans"
							>niemiecki</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_goldstein_lindenmann">Goldstein–Lindenmann</persName>, zboczeniec, ulubieniec <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-Sturmmanna</term> (Podobno jest teraz <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject">aresztowany</term>). Z końcem <date when="1942">1942</date> zostało już tylko 300 Żydów, którzy <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">pracowali</term>
						już pod nadzorem <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-438">Wehrmachtu</orgName>. Po <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">przybyciu</term> (w <date when="1942-12">grudniu 1942</date>) 80 Żydów z
							<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/761168/przemysl.html">Przemyśla</placeName> było już 380 Żydów. Taki stan trwał już do <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573" type="subject">końca</term>. Gdy raz dwaj Żydzi zarzucili powyższemu <persName
							ref="#ehri_et_goldstein_lindenmann">Goldsteinowi–Lindenmannowi</persName>, że <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">bije</term> Żydów, podał, że rzekomo ci dwaj chcą <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">uciekać</term>. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">Zastrzelono</term> ich. W <date when="1943-03">marcu 1943</date> podał listę 56 Żydów jako
						niezdolnych do <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">pracy</term>. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">Rozstrzelano</term> ich. W <date when="1944-07">lipcu 1944 roku</date> podczas
						ofensywy <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004583">sowieckiej</orgName> większość chciała <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">uciec</term>, jednak <persName ref="#ehri_et_goldstein_lindenmann"
							>Goldstein</persName> uniemożliwił im to. Jednak 85 Żydów przemocą wyrwało płoty, nożycami przecięli kolczaste druty i <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">uciekli</term> w las. Tam <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">przebywali</term> 2 tygodnie (do <date when="1944-08-02">2 sierpnia</date>). <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004583">Sowiety</orgName> ich <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573" type="subject">wyzwoliły</term>.</p>
				</div>
				<div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
					<!--<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_munzer_efroim">Efroim Münzer</persName> Testimony (doc.
        301/203)</p>      <p>Original, manuscript, 4 pages, 150 x 210 mm, Polish language</p>-->
					<p><pb facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010203_01.jpg" n="1"/><persName ref="#ehri_et_munzer_efroim">Efroim Münzer</persName>, born <date when="1928-01-01">1. 1. 1928</date> in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/772270/gdow.html">Gdów</placeName>, a town in <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/7533001/wieliczka.html">Wieliczka</placeName> district</p>
					<p>Occupation: baker</p>
					<p>Residence: <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3094802/krakow.html">66/17 Starowiślna [Street]</placeName> in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3094802/krakow.html">Cracow</placeName></p>
					<p>Description of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-486" type="subject">life</term> in <placeName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1878" type="camp">Stalowa Wola</placeName></p>
					<p>He stayed in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term> from <date when="1942">1942</date> to <date when="1944">1944</date>. In <date when="1942-08">August 1942</date>, during a <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-115" type="subject">deportation</term> in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/7533001/wieliczka.html">Wieliczka</placeName>, they were loaded onto <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject">cattle cars</term>, 100 people in each. He rode on a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject">train</term> for 24 hours during a very hot period and nobody
						was allowed to approach them with something to drink. Only in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/7531275/debica.html">Dębica</placeName> a <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_poles" type="subject">Pole</term> gave them a bucket of water at the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660" type="subject">charge</term> of 100 złotys. On the arrival in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term>, they were received by the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-480" type="subject">camp guards</term> consisting of <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_belarusians" type="subject">Belorussians</term> with <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-564"
							type="subject">whips</term>. There were 3 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">barracks</term> for the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1057" type="subject">laborers</term>. In <date when="1942-08"
							>August 1942</date> there were 80 Jews from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/759301/sieniawa.html">Sieniawa</placeName> there. Since <date when="1942-08">August</date>, there were already 680 (600 from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/7533001/wieliczka.html"
							>Wieliczka</placeName>). The bunks in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">barrack</term> had no paillasses, so that the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-558" type="subject">laborers</term>
						slept on the boards. On the first day the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1057" type="subject">workers</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-653" type="subject">stood</term> in front of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">barrack</term> from five in the morning till the evening. During that time they
						were thoroughly searched and deprived of <pb facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010203_02.jpg" n="2"/> everything, from <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660" type="subject">money</term> and valuables down to a simple leather belt. In the evening the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term>
						<foreign xml:lang="de">Scharführer</foreign>
						<persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000364">Schwamberg</persName> (known as the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-551" type="subject">liquidator</term> of the <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/7530748/przemysl.html">Przemyśl</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-546" type="subject">ghetto</term>) and the <foreign xml:lang="de">Unterscharführer</foreign>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_bardok">Brzdok</persName> (probably <persName ref="#ehri_et_bardok">Bardok</persName>) came to them. <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000364">Schwamberg</persName> gave a speech: They have to give away all the
						valuables. Whoever should go near the fence will automatically be <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">shot</term>. Whichever of the Jews talks to a civilian during work, be it about the sale of <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">bread</term> or anything else, will be <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">shot</term>. Whoever pauses at work, will be <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">shot</term>.</p>
					<p>Directly after this speech, the majority threw away the money or <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660" type="subject">valuables</term> they were hiding. In the meantime, as a warning, they <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-653" type="subject">beat</term> several people till blood was drawn, supposedly because they hadn’t given away everything. There was a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-486" type="subject"
							>reveille</term> at two in the night. They marched out to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">work</term> at 6; till then they were kept standing. They were taken away their caps and jackets to prevent them from <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escaping</term>. On the way to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">work</term> in a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-944"
							type="subject">factory</term> distant by 4 km they were driven <pb facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010203_03.jpg" n="3"/> with <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-564" type="subject">whips</term>. They had to run all the way. They <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">worked</term> from 7 am to 6 pm with one 20-minute break at 3 pm for a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">soup</term>. They <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">worked</term> in a steelworks. <foreign xml:lang="de">Vorarbeiters</foreign><note type="gloss">Vorarbeiter (German) – foreman.</note> at <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">work</term> were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1075" type="subject">Volksdeutsche</term>. The greatest sadist among them was <persName ref="#ehri_et_piosik"
							>Piosik</persName> (rumored to come from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/7530858/poznan.html">Poznań</placeName>). He <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">murdered</term> the Jews with a <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-533" type="subject">piece</term> of iron. He once <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-533" type="subject">burned</term> a Jew alive. Most Jews <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">died</term> because of the said <persName ref="#ehri_et_piosik">Piosik</persName>. Almost 8-10 Jews <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escaped</term>
						everyday from the workplace. Because of that almost every day they had to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-653" type="subject">stand</term> 2-3 hours at <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-487" type="subject">roll
							call</term>. In the evening they were given ab[out] <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-834" type="subject">20dkg</term> of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">bread</term> and a <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">soup</term>, in which there were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">dirty</term> and unpeeled <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">potatoes</term>. At the head of a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">barrack</term> stood an <foreign xml:lang="de"
							>Ordnungsdienstmann</foreign>.<note type="gloss">Ordnungsdienstmann (German) – member of the Ordnungsdienst (Order Service)</note> Almost everyday 10-15 of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">sick</term>, who lay in the so
						called <foreign xml:lang="de">Krankenstube</foreign><note type="gloss">Krankenstube (German) - sickroom</note>, were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">shot</term>. These <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">murders</term> were committed by an <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term>-<foreign xml:lang="de">Sturmmann</foreign>. In <date when="1942-12"
							>December 1942</date>, 121 or 123 Jews were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">shot</term> as unfit for <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">work</term>. Apart from that, 10-15
							<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-862" type="subject">people</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">died</term> every day (<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-494" type="subject">dysentery</term> and the like). (Since <date when="1942-09">September</date> there were
						already <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-862" type="subject">1100</term> Jews). <pb facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010203_04.jpg" n="4"/> At the head of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-566" type="subject">OD</term> there stood
						a <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans" type="subject">German</term> Jew, <persName ref="#ehri_et_goldstein_lindenmann">Goldstein-Lindenmann</persName>, a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-840" type="subject">pervert</term>, an <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term>-<foreign xml:lang="de">Sturmmann</foreign>’s favorite (He is rumored to be under <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject">arrest</term> now). At
						the end of <date when="1942">1942</date> only 300 Jews remained, who <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">worked</term> already under the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-438">Wehrmacht’s</orgName>
						supervision. After 80 Jews from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/7530748/przemysl.html">Przemyśl</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">arrived</term> (in <date when="1942-12">December 1942</date>), there were already 380 Jews. This situation didn’t change until <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573"
							type="subject">the end</term>. Once, when two Jews accused the said <persName ref="#ehri_et_goldstein_lindenmann">Goldstein-Lindenmann</persName> of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">beating</term> the Jews, he <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-200" type="subject">denounced</term> their supposed intention of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escape</term>. They were <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">shot</term>. In <date when="1943-03">March 1943</date> he prepared a list of 56 Jews who, as he claimed, were unable to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943"
							type="subject">work</term>. They were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">shot</term>. In <date when="1944-07">July 1944</date>, during the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004583">Soviet
							offensive</orgName>, most people wanted to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escape</term>, but were prevented by <persName ref="#ehri_et_goldstein_lindenmann">Goldstein</persName>. And yet 85 Jews pulled out the fences, cut
						the barbed wire with scissors and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">ran away</term> into the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">forest</term>. They <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">stayed</term> there for 2 weeks (until <date when="1945-08-02">August 2</date>). They were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573" type="subject">liberated</term> by the
							<orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004583">Soviets</orgName>.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
